derivation: or אִתְמוֹל; or אֶתְמוּל; probably from H853 (אֵת) or H854 (אֵת) and H4136 (מוּל);
outline:
1. yesterday, recently, formerly
    1. yesterday
    2. formerly (fig.)
    3. from yesterday, already (in phrase)
  2. (TWOT +) before, before that time, before the time, heretofore, of late, of old, these days, time(s) past
kjv_def: [phrase] before (that) time, [phrase] heretofore, of late (old), [phrase] times past, yester(day).
